The paper deals with approximating stochastic matchings, which is a problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and game theory (cs.GT). The authors also use techniques from machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) to solve the problem. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of LP (linear programming) techniques, which is a common tool in optimization and operations research (cs.SI).
